---
import DocLayout from "../../layouts/DocLayout.astro";
---

<DocLayout
  title="Documentation"
  eyebrow="Docs"
  description="Reference for the OpenPress framework — CLI commands, the Press / Frame / MdxArea primitives, MDX source configuration, the workspace Manifest schema, and the product boundary that decides whether OpenPress fits your workflow."
>
  <p>
    These docs lock down two things: <em>where OpenPress sits in your workflow</em>, and
    <em>which APIs are safe to depend on after 1.0</em>. Anything reachable in source but not listed here
    is treated as internal and may change in a minor release.
  </p>

  <div class="doc-grid">
    <a class="doc-card" href="/docs/product-boundary">
      <p class="doc-card__eyebrow">Start here</p>
      <h3>Product boundary</h3>
      <p>What lives in OpenPress, what doesn't, and which tool to reach for instead.</p>
    </a>

    <a class="doc-card" href="/docs/cli">
      <p class="doc-card__eyebrow">CLI</p>
      <h3>Commands</h3>
      <p><code>init</code>, <code>dev</code>, <code>export</code>, <code>render</code>, <code>pdf</code>, <code>deploy</code>, <code>search</code>, <code>replace</code>, and friends.</p>
    </a>

    <a class="doc-card" href="/docs/api/press">
      <p class="doc-card__eyebrow">Component</p>
      <h3>Press</h3>
      <p>The document composition boundary — one Press wraps every Frame in your tree.</p>
    </a>

    <a class="doc-card" href="/docs/api/frame">
      <p class="doc-card__eyebrow">Component</p>
      <h3>Frame</h3>
      <p>One fixed page surface. Covers, content pages, slides, and social cards are all Frames.</p>
    </a>

    <a class="doc-card" href="/docs/api/mdx-area">
      <p class="doc-card__eyebrow">Component</p>
      <h3>MdxArea</h3>
      <p>A measurable slot inside a Frame that the engine fills with allocated blocks.</p>
    </a>

    <a class="doc-card" href="/docs/api/manuscript">
      <p class="doc-card__eyebrow">Helpers</p>
      <h3>Manuscript</h3>
      <p><code>Sections</code> + <code>Toc</code> — optional helpers for long-form section flow.</p>
    </a>

    <a class="doc-card" href="/docs/api/sources">
      <p class="doc-card__eyebrow">Data</p>
      <h3>MDX & sources</h3>
      <p>How <code>mdxSource()</code> and the <code>sources</code> export wire content into the engine.</p>
    </a>

    <a class="doc-card" href="/docs/config">
      <p class="doc-card__eyebrow">Config</p>
      <h3>Workspace config</h3>
      <p>The <code>Manifest</code> schema — metadata, page geometry, source folders, captions, deploy.</p>
    </a>

    <a class="doc-card" href="/docs/public-api">
      <p class="doc-card__eyebrow">Reference</p>
      <h3>API surface index</h3>
      <p>The full list of what's stable for 1.0 and what's explicitly internal.</p>
    </a>
  </div>

  <h2>Conventions</h2>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Component / Hook / Function / Type</strong> badges mark each API entry's kind.</li>
    <li>Props tables list <em>name · type · default · description</em>. The <code>required</code> tag is shown next to the name.</li>
    <li>Every entry includes an import line and at least one usage example.</li>
    <li>Anything outside the API pages — deep imports, internal helpers — is <strong>not</strong> covered by 1.0 stability.</li>
  </ul>
</DocLayout>

<style>
  .doc-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(15rem, 1fr));
    gap: var(--op-space-4);
    margin: var(--op-space-6) 0 var(--op-space-8);
  }

  .doc-card {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.4rem;
    padding: var(--op-space-5);
    border: 1px solid var(--op-hairline);
    border-radius: 6px;
    background: var(--op-surface);
    color: var(--op-ink);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition:
      border-color 140ms ease,
      transform 140ms ease,
      box-shadow 140ms ease;
  }
  .doc-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--op-accent);
    transform: translateY(-1px);
    box-shadow: 0 2px 12px color-mix(in srgb, var(--op-ink) 6%, transparent);
  }
  .doc-card__eyebrow {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--op-subdued);
    font-family: var(--op-font-mono);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  .doc-card h3 {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: var(--op-font-body);
    font-size: var(--op-text-lg);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--op-ink-strong);
  }
  .doc-card p {
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--op-subdued-strong);
    font-size: var(--op-text-sm);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .doc-card p code {
    padding: 0.06em 0.3em;
    border-radius: 3px;
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--op-ink) 7%, transparent);
    font-family: var(--op-font-mono);
    font-size: 0.85em;
  }
</style>
